<TITLE> Morshed Khan, Manju secure bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 18 (bdnews24.com)Former foreign minister M Morshed Khan and former communications minister Anwar Hossain Manju both sentenced to jail for corruptionsecured bail on Monday from the High Court. The bench of justices Md Wahhab Miah and Marji Ul Haq granmted them bail until the appeals against their sentences are disposed of. Khan was convicted of stashing illegal wealth while Manju on two counts for taking bribe. On Dec 10, 2007, Anticorruption Commission filed a case against Khan on the charge of accumulating wealth illegally. He was sentenced to 13 years in prison in absentia on Aug 4 , 2008. Khan, an adviser to the main opposition BNP chairperson, was sent to jail on May 10 after he surrendered to the trial court. The case was filed against Manju with Shahbagh Police Station on charge of taking Tk 77 lakh as bribe on July 25, 2007. In the case, he was sentenced to 7 years in prison on June 10, 2008. Another case was filed against him with Dhanmondi Police Station on the allegation of taking Tk 1 crore in bribe on July 25, 2007. In the case he was sentenced to a further 7 years in jail on May 28, 2008 . At the directive of the High Court, on May 7 he surrendered to the trial court which ordered him into jail During the hearing, barrister Rafique-Ul Haque argued for Khan and Manju while deputy attorney general ASM Mubin represented the state. b
